HEADWORD: Curialistic
<hw>Cu`ri*a*lis"tic</hw> <pr>(-l?s"t?k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[L.<ets>curialis</ets> belonging to the imperial court, fr.
<ets>curia</ets>, LL., also, counselors and retinue of a king.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Pertaining to a court.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Relating or belonging to the ultramontane party in
the Latin Church.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Curiality</ent>⟦br⟧
